acPersonItem PersonId="20419" RecordID="022-000008141">Lupi,Orazio,,</ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20420" RecordID="022-000008142">Selvaggio,Massimiliano,,</ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20421" RecordID="022-000008143">Massarengo,Giovanni Battista,,</ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20422" RecordID="022-000008144">Carretto,Oderico,,</ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20101" RecordID="022-000007603">Ceba`,Ansaldo,,1565-1623</ItacPersonItem></Contributors><Notes>The volume records celebrations that took place at the palace of Count Alfonso Beccaria in Pavia on 1st May, 1590. Although the assembly that met on this occasion is not referred to explicitly as an academy, many academies feature in the text, including the Cospiranti (Treviso), Invaghiti (Mantua), Crusca(Florence), Addormentati (Genoa), Desiosi (Pavia), Innominati (Parma), and Illustrati (Casale Monferrato).
In a verse dedicated to the book (`Sopra la Ghirlanda`) by Antonio Acciali, in the preface, an allusion is made to Guazzo`s nickname in the Accademia degli Illustrati, Elevato. The first tercet reads: `GUAZZO gentil, Cigno immortal canoro, / Che di Poemi altrui l`opra inalzasti, / Godi l&#224; suso, ove ELEVATO siedi.`</Notes><Dedicatees><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20423" RecordID="022-000008145">Beccaria,Angela Bianca,,</ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20424" RecordID="022-000008146">Guazzo,Olimpia,,</ItacPersonItem></Dedicatees><Editors><ItacPersonItem PersonId="9194" RecordID="022-000001773">Guazzo,Stefano,,1530-1593</ItacPersonItem></Editors><Printers><ItacPersonItem PersonId="20506" RecordID="022-000008245">Bartoli (eredi di),Girolamo,,fl. 1575-1596</ItacPersonItem></Printers><PrinterOrnament>U109</PrinterOrnament><Citation>Lorenza Gianfrancesco and Simone Testa, directed by Jane Everson, Denis Reidy, Lisa Sampson, assisted by Thomas Denman, for the Italian Academies Database project.</Citation></ItacWorkItem>